CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 4, 1961, pg. 24 reads: "Staged Their First Affair - These six officers (seated) of Alpha Phi Beta Sorority, a charming group of high school girls, staged their initial affair at the East Liberty YMCA recently. Mrs. Yvonne Kemp (standing, at left) served as chaperone.  Left to right: Veronica Gloster, social chairman; Iris Keys, publicity chairman; Elaine Drake, president; Karen Kemp, treasurer, and Cheryl Harris, secretary.  Standing at extreme right is Mrs. Betty Tibbs, sponsor of the sorority. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Beta sorority members, from left: chaperone Yvonne Jones Kemp, Veronica Gloster, Iris Keys, Elaine Drake, Karen Kemp, Cheryl Harris, and sponsor Betty Tibbs, all wearing ribbons, posed possibly East Liberty YMCA, with checkered linoleum floor
